Steps to do before run AMS02(v4.00/v5.00)  MC Standalone Client on intel/amd computers running  Linux


copy attached file to {somedir}
(optional)
download v6.00mcdb.tar.gz and  v6.00mcdb.addon.tar.gz files from 
http://pcamss0.cern.ch/cgi-bin/mon/download.o.cgi to {somedir}

In case the specified version of executable is nopt in tar file,

All executibles can also be found in /afs/cern.ch/ams/Offline/AMSDataDir/DataManagement/exe/linux


IMPORTANT

please always delete all your DataBase staff before untaring  v6.00mcdb.addon.tar.gz

cd {somedir}
tar -xzvf v6.00mcscripts.tar.gz
(optional)
tar -xzvf v6.00mcdb.tar.gz
rm -rf DataBase
tar -xzvf v6.00mcdb.addon.tar.gz

geant4 related data -> please deploy geant4 from /afs/cern.ch/exp/ams/Offline/geant4.9.3.p02/data to geant4_local_path if needed

/bin/sh


export G4INSTALL=geant4_local_path
export G4LEVELGAMMADATA=$G4INSTALL/data/PhotonEvaporation2.1
export G4DPMJET2_5DATA=$G4INSTALL/data/DPMJET/GlauberData
export G4RADIOACTIVEDATA=$G4INSTALL/data/RadioactiveDecay3.3
export G4LEDATA=$G4INSTALL/data/G4EMLOW6.19
export NeutronHPCrossSections=$G4INSTALL/data/G4NDL3.14
export G4ELASTIC=$G4INSTALL/data/G4ELASTIC1.1
export G4NEUTRONXSDATA=$G4INSTALL/data/G4NEUTRONXS1.0
export G4PIIDATA=$G4INSTALL/data/G4PII1.2



/bin/sh
ulimit -d 2000000
ulimit -s 64000
export AMSDataDir=`pwd`
export ExeDir=`pwd`/exe
export CERN_ROOT=`pwd`
export NtupleDir={somedirWithAtLeast20GBytesFreeSpace}


nice -20 {script1...n}.job 1>{script1...n.log} 2>&1 &



Exceptions handling:

a. Your job was killed because of batch system timelimit.
   Do not try to restart the job.
   Proceed as in normal case, i.e. transfer dst and journal files to CERN.
   
b. Your job was killed because of "segmentation violation" 
   Please send job log file to v.choutko@cern.ch   
   Do not try to restart the job.
   Proceed as in normal case, i.e. transfer dst and journal files to CERN.

c.  Your job was killed because of "ZFATAL" 
    goto a.


NB

export ProductionLogDir=some_dir  allows you to redirect journal files  to
some_dir/MCProducer


NB1

if you prefer to write DST files to a local (tmp) disk and then to transfer it
to some permanent place you have to additionally define

export NtupleDestDir={somedir}
export TransferBy="cp "   (rfcp if you are going to copy to HPSS-like volumes)


NB2
You have to copy the resulted DST from $NtupleDir together with
journal file(s) from AMSDataDir/prod.log/MCProducer/{RunNumber}.journal
to AMS-CERN computers manually.  Please contact a.eline@cern.ch
about available/recommended data transfer software.


 

DST directory path : /eos/ams/MC/scratch/test/nt
                
 Journal files directory path : /eos/ams/MC/scratch/test/jou
                
 Validation log files directory path : /eos/ams/MC/scratch/test/log
                
